(PURPOSE) Tj
0 -14 Td
() Tj
0 -14 Td
(This procedure covers weekly inspection and light service of the fictional E18 electric) Tj
0 -14 Td
(forklift battery bay. It focuses on cable condition, connector heat, hold-down hardware,) Tj
0 -14 Td
(residue cleanup, and ventilation path integrity.) Tj
0 -14 Td
() Tj
0 -14 Td
(The procedure is intended for trained maintenance technicians and shift leads. Production) Tj
0 -14 Td
(operators may assist with observation and restart confirmation, but they do not perform) Tj
0 -14 Td
(isolated service work unless the task card explicitly allows it.) Tj
0 -14 Td
() Tj
0 -14 Td
(REQUIRED TOOLS AND PARTS) Tj
0 -14 Td
() Tj
0 -14 Td
(- Insulated hand tools, terminal brush, neutral cleaning solution, absorbent pads, inspection) Tj
0 -14 Td
(mirror, and torque wrench.) Tj
0 -14 Td
(- Replacement vent caps, cable ties rated for battery compartments, and approved dielectric) Tj
0 -14 Td
(grease.) Tj
0 -14 Td
(- Acid-resistant gloves, face shield, splash apron, and battery service checklist.) Tj
0 -14 Td
(- Portable fan for added airflow during extended inspection if the charging area is warm or) Tj
0 -14 Td
(enclosed.) Tj
0 -14 Td
() Tj
0 -14 Td
(HAZARDS AND CONTROLS) Tj
0 -14 Td
() Tj
0 -14 Td
(- Wear acid-resistant PPE before opening the bay, even if no leak is visible.) Tj
0 -14 Td
(- Do not place metal tools on the battery top or bridge positive and negative terminals with a) Tj
0 -14 Td
(loose part or rag.) Tj
0 -14 Td
(- If swelling, cracked cases, or strong sulfur odor are present, stop work and escalate to the) Tj
0 -14 Td
(fleet supervisor immediately.) Tj
0 -14 Td
(- Use neutral cleaner only on approved surfaces and keep liquids away from control modules) Tj
0 -14 Td
(mounted above the battery tray.) Tj
0 -14 Td
() Tj
0 -14 Td
(PREPARATION) Tj
0 -14 Td
() Tj
0 -14 Td
(- Park the truck in the designated service lane, key off, chock the wheels, and confirm no) Tj
0 -14 Td
(active charging cable is attached.) Tj
0 -14 Td
(- Open the battery bay and inspect hold-downs, tray rails, cable strain relief, and vent cap) Tj
0 -14 Td
(seating before touching residue.) Tj
ET
